Banque Nationale de Paris said its profit rose 13% in the first half of 1989, reflecting continued brisk loan demand and tight budget control. 

The commercial bank group, France's biggest in terms of total assets, said group profit after payments to minority interests rose to 1.475 billion francs ($232.3 million) from 1.308 billion francs in the first half of 1988. 

BNP noted that net banking income, which covers its income from lending, trading and commissions, climbed 15% in the first half to 17.576 billion francs. 

